From Ed Hew Subject newsgroups mlists FAQ periodic posting Evolution of SCO newsgroups and Mailing Lists Many readers enjoyed the opportunity to obtain and contribute useful information on SCO Open Desktop since through the ancestral USENET newsgroup or it's companion mailing Similarly there was a demonstrated need for an information and discussion forum for SCO products in With the increasing demand for accessibility and for additional SCO newsgroups many current contributors including those who have been active in circulating SCO related newsgroups and mailing lists felt that the readership would be best served by creating a hierarchy to improve propagation and hence availability opendesktop general announce were newgrouped May in accordance with accepted procedure within biz Given the content this change relocated the opendesktop newsgroup to a more proper place within the established usenet news hierarchy and adds the new announce and general On Aug the former became scogen in keeping with established naming and were newgrouped on June to respectively accommodate SCO Xenix UNIX and OpenDesktop specific binaries and source The binaries and sources news groups are moderated with moderator and submissions information and policy outlined in the periodic imformational postings in those Respecting USENET etiquite these newsgroups are not gated to mailing lists but are archived on several nuucp and ftp was newgrouped Dec to provide a discussion area for the readers writers and publishers of SCO Subject to the USENET NEWS hierarchies carried by your upstream feed you are now able to subscribe to the following Newsgroup mailing list subscription none none You are strongly encouraged to obtain these newsgroups via USENET NEWS mechanisms vrs Anyone having difficulty arranging a news feed for these newsgroups is welcome to email the undersigned and I'll do my best to We also offer all required software in source code form via anonymous FTP and UUCP as do many archive If aft